Thailand's long zig-zag struggle for democracy is threatening to become a farce with dire implications for all Southeast Asia.

As the only Southeast Asian country never colonized by a Western power, Thailand is proud of its independence before and since the end of absolute monarchy in 1932. But Thais never learned from farangs (foreigners) how to make democracy work.
